📸 Finally Back and Ready to Share!

Hey everyone! 👋 It's been a while since I last posted, and I apologize for the radio silence. Life has been quite a whirlwind lately, but I'm thrilled to be back and ready to showcase some incredible shots that I've captured recently. As a wedding portrait photographer, my passion lies in immortalizing those beautiful moments of love and joy, and I can't wait to share them with all of you!

Firstly, let me fill you in on what's been happening behind the scenes. I had the amazing opportunity to visit Costa Rica on Mathis’s birthday It was truly tremendous.

I returned home but Alaia and Papa felt sick for almost two weeks 😫 Now it's time to post again I've gotten stunning shoots to post.

So, get ready for a flood of wedding portraits that will make your heart skip a beat. Each image tells a unique love story, and I hope they inspire you as much as they've inspired me. Thank you for your patience and understanding during this hiatus. Your support means the world to me, and I can't wait to embark on this incredible journey with all of you once again.

Stay tuned, my friends! The best is yet to come. ❤️

#WeddingPortraits #BackAndBetter #CapturingLove #PhotographyPassion #IncredibleMoments #StayTuned

The warm golden light, the cozy sweaters, and the crunch of leaves underfoot all add an extra layer of magic to every shot. It's like nature is putting on its own spectacular show, and I'm just lucky enough to be there to capture it. 

So, my friends, get ready to embrace the beauty of fall with open arms! Whether you're planning a family photoshoot, an engagement session, or simply want to capture the essence of this incredible season.

I want to talk about something that adds an extra sprinkle of magic to the already enchanting journey of becoming a bride - the post-wedding photoshoot!!

Your wedding day is undoubtedly one of the most beautiful moments of your life. But let's be honest, it can also be a whirlwind of emotions and excitement. A post-wedding photoshoot allows you to relive those magical moments in a more relaxed and intimate setting.

A post-wedding photoshoot gives you the opportunity to showcase your bridal beauty in a whole new light.
With no time constraints or wedding day chaos, you can experiment with different outfits, locations, and poses. Your wedding day is just the beginning of a beautiful journey with your partner. A post-wedding photoshoot allows you to embark on new adventures together, capturing your love story against breathtaking backdrops.

Time flies, and memories fade, but photographs are forever. A post-wedding photoshoot ensures that you have a treasure trove of memories to cherish for a lifetime. These stunning images will become a tangible reminder of the love, joy, and happiness you felt on your special day. Whenever you need a dose of nostalgia, just flip through those albums and let the memories come flooding back!

Grooms, it's time to shine!

Your presence on your wedding day is absolutely crucial, not just for your lovely bride, but also for those incredible photos that will freeze those magical moments in time. Here's why:

Your wedding day is all about the love and connection you share with your partner. By being fully present, you allow the photographer to capture the genuine emotions, laughter, and joy that radiate between you two.

A complete wedding album is all about balance. Having both the bride and groom equally represented in the photos creates a harmonious visual story. Your presence ensures that the album reflects the true essence of your special day.

Supporting your partner: Your bride has put in so much effort to make this day perfect, and your presence by her side is a testament to your love and commitment.

by being available for photos, you show your support and make her feel even more special. Plus, those candid shots of you two together will be absolutely priceless!
So, grooms, let's make sure we're fully present and ready to shine on our wedding day! Your active participation in the photography process will result in a stunning collection of memories that will be cherished for generations to come.

Peace & love 

#GroomsOnPoint #WeddingDayJoy #CapturingLove

Gratitude is the quality of being thankful and appreciative for the things we have in life. It is a positive emotion that acknowledges the goodness and blessings we receive, whether big or small. 

Practicing gratitude can lead to increased happiness, improved relationships, and a more positive outlook on life. It involves recognizing and expressing appreciation for the people, experiences, and things that bring joy and fulfillment. Gratitude can be cultivated through daily practices. @cardozoaleja know more it than me, if you don’t know how practice it she can help you.

Ver un hermano luego de casi 5 años, Trabajar en la primera fábrica, mesonero, mi primera sesión en Chicago, manejar para Uber, lift contratado como Fotografo en los colegios de Illinois y Wisconsin, delivery y más delivery,  luego una mueblería levantando muebles de los picapiedras jajajaja pesados!! 

Todo eso pasaba con un inglés Machucao, frustración, depresión, ganas de devolverme, extrañar, muchas ganas de abrazar a mi mama, muchas ganas de estar con mathias, 9 viajes, ego al piso, primera vez en un quirófano, una cirugía bucal, mucha lloradera, muchas risas, también soledad, extrañando la playa, el surf, el tomar fotos en sandalias y shorts, pocos pero buenos amigos, pandemia, miedo, muchos insultos, mucha gente rara.

Se dicen en poquitas líneas todo esto, pero no fue tan tan fácil, pensé en un momento “no lo lograré, pero bueno, Seguí. 

Hoy no lo comento por lamento, al contrario me molesta el quejón, Hoy lo digo para recordarme o recordarte que todo tiene su tiempo, lo que un día soñaba hoy es una realidad, Hoy es es para darme mi palmadita, para decirme Gracias, para abrazarme y agradecer a todos los que me han acompañado en esto llamado vida y especialmente a ti @fabicfl porque bueno acá seguimos con muchos bajos pero muchos mas arribas!! 🙏🏻

TODAY I became a citizen of The United States luego de casi 7 años en un país que nos abrió las puertas, mucho que agradecerle a este lugar, que con trabajo honesto y siendo perseverante los sueños se pueden convertir en una realidad. 

En fin hoy me digo de pana eres un duro, recuerdas cuando no quisiste ser un Fotografo sino un artista, recuerdas esa decisión ?? Que te dijiste a pesar de lo que pasara, trataría de dar lo mejor de ti para seguir siendo lo que quería ser, pues mírate acá hoy con una ciudadanía en un lugar que sentías imposible, con un idioma que no te entraba, Hoy con una bienvenida y recordándote que lo que quieres, siempre puedes,  lo último que te digo es me caes bien mi pana aunque a veces me hace arreeee…. aa.  jajaja 

Thanks 🇺🇸
@neyer & @jeffrey.m.morrison Wedding 🙏🏻

“Always and always” I ask to myself what I can do more,  how I find a meaning for my job, I mean I just don't want to be this photographer who hears just Omg I look so pretty. 

I won't say the names here of respect and admiration for this couple,  their story is so precious, She is 40 and He is 70, their love is different, her one heart birthday surgery she had an appointment to get a photoshoot with me, she was celebrating her life, she didn't know if she would breath again, the photos are incredible, the vibes is unique, She poses for her gentleman and He hire me for watch his woman posing almost naked in different and luxury hotel rooms, they love to love. 

I want more than I love the photos because I look pretty, I know that everyone wants to look handsome even me!! But when I am getting more experience for not say ages, there are constant questions around of my head, questions like: what can I do more for us like humans, why I should follow a group if everyone has their own flow. 

I wish to keep being part of them and those stories that are sincerely where love is love, and not a fake to get more likes!!

Feliz cumpleaños a mi Puyipuyi!! 

No se ni como comenzar pero bueno acá intentaré describir lo que desde tu nacimiento ha sido, tu me enseñaste por segunda vez lo bonito y escalofriante que es ser padre, cuando me refiero a “ segunda vez” no se trata de ningún lugar, tú y Mathias son y serán siempre mi primer lugar, lo que trato de decir es que Gracias, Gracias por ser tu, gracias por escogerme, gracias por ser la mejor escaladora, la risueña mas bella del planeta,  Gracias por esos besos con baba, Gracias por prestarme tu pies para olerlo y morderlos GRACIAS por EXISTIR.

Hoy es tu primer añito, un año que se ha convertido en entender que la vida a veces la vivimos atentos de tonterías que al final, todo lo que tenemos es suficiente y Hoy es todo lo que tenemos, Hoy estamos bien, incluso el abuelo que está con unos doctores, Hoy tenemos Vida, Hoy te dijimos Feliz cumpleaños, aunque es verdad no todos los días son bonitos, sobre todo cuando tengo muchas entregas de galerías , La verdad, verdad no cambiaría nada o quizás un poquitín para que no me pellizques tan duro, jajaja mentira esas pinzitas de mano son preciosas.
